# Microplastic Detector using ESP32 and IoT

## 📌 Project Overview
This project is designed to detect microplastics in water using an ESP32 microcontroller. It monitors water flow, turbidity, and plastic presence using sensors, displays the results on a TFT display, and uploads the data to ThingSpeak for real-time monitoring.

## 🎯 Objective
To develop a low-cost IoT-based system for detecting microplastics in water and monitoring water quality.

## ⚙️ Components Used
- ESP32
- Turbidity Sensor
- Water Flow Sensor
- Laser Sensor
- ST7735 TFT Display
- ThingSpeak Cloud Platform

## ✨ Features
- Real-time water quality monitoring
- Plastic detection using a laser sensor
- Water flow measurement
- TFT display for live results
- Cloud data logging with ThingSpeak

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Arduino IDE
- Embedded C++
- IoT
- ThingSpeak

